{{BookCat}}

{{B3D:N2P/NAV
|next=Model a Chair-Preparations
|previous=
}}

Now let's start with real modeling. In this tutorial we will study in greater depth how to model using box modeling work flow. Let start with a swan chair. It is great piece to model for its a popular piece of furniture so reference images are easy to find. It also have a simple geometric structure so its shape easy to grasp and also contains simple edge and face loop flow so as not to necessitate difficult edge loop face loop flow herding techniques.

{{Noframecenter|1=[[Image:SwanChairSceneInBlender.png|400px]]|2=Scene with the chair model as seen in Blender}}

{{Noframecenter|1=[[Image:SwanChairSceneRenderedWithBlender.jpg|400px]]|2=Rendered Scene with the chair}}

The techniques learned could also be used to model other chairs (Example: the Egg chair, Tulip chair or Parson's chair which is advised to be modeled too) and other subjects.

{{B3D:N2P/NAV
|next=Model a Chair-Preparations
|previous=
}}

