==Description==
===Visual effect===
* changes the color of the next objects to be drawn
[[image:OpenGL_Programming_reference_glColor.png]]
==Usage Context==
* Will work anywhere in Display loop but normally used between [[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glBegin|glBegin]] and [[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glEnd|glEnd]].
* Affects everything following until it is called again or the loop starts over.
* [[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glEnd|glEnd]](); and [[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glBegin|glBegin]](); do not affect it.

==Usage Examples==
* draws 7 points and 3 different colors
* starting from x center  y .5+  and moving to  x .6+ y .5+
* shows that the color will stay even if you restart a new gl section
* shows that the color will stay even if the loop starts over
* replace the display function with this in the [[OpenGL_Programming/reference/basic_testing_app|basic testing app]] program to see the results

 void display(void)
 {
 	[[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glClear|glClear]]([[OpenGL_Programming/reference/GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT|GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT]] | [[OpenGL_Programming/reference/GL_DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT|GL_DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT]]);
 	[[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glBegin|glBegin]]([[OpenGL_Programming/reference/GL_POINTS|GL_POINTS]]);
 		[[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glVertex3f|glVertex3f]](0.0,0.5,0.0);//drawn white or default color first loop and green all other loops
 		[[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glColor3f|glColor3f]](1.0,0.5,0.0);//set red 100% green 50% blue 0%
 		[[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glVertex3f|glVertex3f]](0.1,0.5,0.0);//drawn orange
 		[[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glVertex3f|glVertex3f]](0.2,0.5,0.0);//drawn orange
 		[[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glColor3f|glColor3f]](1.0,0.0,0.0);//set red 100% green 0% blue 0%
 		[[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glVertex3f|glVertex3f]](0.3,0.5,0.0);//drawn red
 	[[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glEnd|glEnd]]();
 	[[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glBegin|glBegin]]([[OpenGL_Programming/reference/GL_POINTS|GL_POINTS]]);
 		[[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glVertex3f|glVertex3f]](0.4,0.5,0.0);//drawn red
 		[[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glColor3f|glColor3f]](0.0,1.0,0.0);//set red 0% green 100% blue 0%
 		[[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glVertex3f|glVertex3f]](0.5,0.5,0.0);//drawn green
 		[[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glVertex3f|glVertex3f]](0.6,0.5,0.0);//drawn green
 	[[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glEnd|glEnd]]();
 	[[OpenGL_Programming/reference/glutSwapBuffers|glutSwapBuffers]]();
 }

